* Violates established secure design principles, introducing weaknesses or making them easier to introduce later
* Related to improper coding standards, unnecessary complexity, obscurity reliance
* Examples: switches exposing traffic when tables overflow, IPSEC complexity bugs, SSO account compromise impact 
* Principles violated: economy of mechanism, complete mediation, psychological acceptability 
